	     <form action="/cgi-bin/mrate.pl" name="f105357450325528">
	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=20085&amp;mid=105357450325528">Spawn information</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=20085&amp;mid=105357450325528#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Thu, May 22nd 12:16 AM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=154752"><span id=" ">Merrith</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">8 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>The 4 stats that influence this item are 1h blunt, 2h blunt, hand to hand, and piercing (max 110 for all 4).&nbsp;&nbsp;With none maxed it has 0 stats.  With 1 makes it has 3mana 1fire/disease. With 2 maxed it has 1ac 1int 1agi 7mana 4fire/disease.  With 3 maxed it has 1ac 2int 2agi 10mana 4fire/disease.  With all 4 it is 3ac 5int 5agi 20mana 8fire/disease.<br/><br/>The name of the mob who drops this is Scryer Xvallos.  He spawns in a small &quot;pool room&quot; in the northern section of Torgiran mines.  If you zone in from Dulak you'll be in the very south in the actual &quot;mine section&quot;.  Just before the pool room there's an L corner just before the door leading down that has no spawns or wanderers there.  Inside there room there are 5 mobs: two on the right, one on the left, two in the back.  I did the camp with me (65 wizard) and my dual box (62 mage).  If you don't have pacify, note that the first two on the right will both come even with a level 65 puller, so root one, kill the add, then wait for the other.  You can then single the one on the left, but you'll have to root pull the last two in the back as well.<br/><br/>The mobs there are either a luggald abomination, a luggald arcanist (wizard), a luggald occultist, or a luggald reaver (shadow knight).  Highest I saw them hit for was around 149, each has about 10k-12k life.  The wizard I saw cast the following spells: lure of frost, ice comet, rend, atol's spectral shackles, draught of fire, and tishan's discord.  The shadowed knight's Harm Touch sucks but as far as spells I only saw him cast Insidious Regression, Dooming Darkness, and a lifetap.  Scryer Xvallos spawned on the 39th mob (was back right mob on 8th cycle of clearing).  Scryer is an enchanter mob that cast Fascination and Gasping Embrace (didn't give him a chance to cast any others).  He mezzed my mage pretty fast so I just dropped him with root and nuke on the wizard, and it took ~4 Strike of Soluseks to drop him (12k hp).  Dropped only the charm for me on his first spawn luckily.  Rest of them only dropped Luggald daggers/tridents and a stackable claw shards (assume they're sellable to vendor).<br/><br/>Hope this post helps any seeking the charm.</p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
