	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=20085&amp;mid=110244569068160">RE: Hmmm...  (Poll)</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=20085&amp;mid=110244569068160#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Tue, Dec 7th 1:55 PM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=183975"><span id=" ">Tomojo</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">11 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Absolutely.... That Extended Range III once the stats are maxed is priceless in this slot.<br/><br/>In fact, skilling up is quite easy, though a bit tedious....<br/><br/>Most wizzies will have probably maxed skill in 1hb and piercing, some may have skilled up in 2HB as well, but most probably ignore H2H and Throwing. Even if they aren't they can easily be maxed using the same method described here.<br/><br/>Skilling up can easily be done once you have snare. Find a safe place where you can pull a mob that will go into a death walk when less than 20% health. Grab a single 'blue' mob and get it to the safe area, root and snare it, then nuke away till it is in a death walk (standing still).&nbsp;&nbsp;Start with a one or 2 big nukes, then use smaller ones to make sure you don't overblast right past the deathwalk and kill it.<br/><br/>At this point you can use any weapon to just whack away for skill points. You just have to make sure that you reapply the snare before it starts its death walk. If it gets to 1% health, switch to H2H, and it will slowly regain health as it is almost impossible to hit it often or for enough damage to kill it using H2H. If it gets over 19% health, use a very small nuke to bring it back down to around 16/17, the Solists Icy Wand is perfect for this only because it saves mana for re-snaring.<br/><br/>It will probably be easier if you also have 'harvest' and cast it every time it becomes available to avoid running out of mana. You should be able to keep the mob in the standing deathwalk forver if you have the patience.<br/><br/>I was able to bring 2HB and H2H from 15 (trained) to max skill in about 6 hours time doing this.  It took about another 1hr and 20 minutes to bring Throwing from 1 all the way to Max as the skillups for throwing come much faster than for pure melee skillups. I started with 2 10 slot backpacks full of throwing knives and had more than 3 stacks left when skill maxed. <br/><br/>At 56, I did this in Cobalt Scar using the Wyverns, where you could do this as low as 48-50. In the 30s or low 40s, it could be done on the Ulthork in Eastern Wastes. Find wherever you are comfortable.<br/><br/>Now if I could only find some way to reasonably safely max Defense.......<br/></p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
